<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-23T15:04:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-23T15:04:00-05:00" n="1282" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1282">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3353.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi> (<hi rend="italic">via El Paso,
                                        Tex.</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-23T13:00:00-07:04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The provisional government demands the mine taxes due to the Federal
                            Government at the close of this month. Penalty according to law for
                            nonpayment 50 per cent increase first month, 100 second, relinquishment
                            title third. While larger mines can stand double payment in case of
                            failure of rebel movement, it will be burdensome for many small owners.
                            I respectfully ask advice.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>